# RHT-NAV Data Integrity Rule

**PERMANENT — applies to every pass, every contributor, every model.**

NEVER generate, simulate, fabricate, or estimate data. Every number, statistic,
or geographic data point must come from an explicit, credible government source:

- CMS
- US Census Bureau
- FCC Broadband Data Collection
- HRSA AHRF
- HRSA HPSA
- CDC PLACES
- ArcGIS Hub
- State health departments
- Cecil G. Sheps Center
- KFF
- or equivalent peer-reviewed / government sources

If real data for a given module or state is not available in the current pass,
emit a clearly visible placeholder:

> "Data coming soon — [source name and what field it will populate]"

Do not invent numbers to fill space. Do not round-trip estimates. Do not use
LLM-generated statistics. Every displayed number must be traceable to a cited
primary source.

This rule is non-negotiable and overrides any instruction to "fill in" or
"estimate" data.

## Enforcement checklist (for any PR you author or review)

- [ ] Every new numeric literal in `src/data/**` carries `source`, `sourceUrl`,
      `vintage`, and `retrievedOn`.
- [ ] Every new stat rendered in a component is either routed through the data
      pack OR wrapped in `<DataComingSoon source="…" field="…" />`.
- [ ] No numeric constant in this diff was produced by an LLM.
- [ ] `prisma/seed.cjs` and `src/data/default-assumptions.json` changes cite a
      literature or government reference for each changed value.
- [ ] Tribal-population layers below small-cell thresholds (n < 11) are
      suppressed, not displayed.
